Let $A B C$ be a triangle with altitude $\overline{A F}$. Let $A B=5, A C=8, B C=7$. Let $P$ be on $\overline{A F}$ such that it lies between $A$ and $F$. Let $\omega_{1}, \omega_{2}$ be the circumcircles of $A P B, A P C$ respectively. Let $\overline{B C}$ intersect $\omega_{1}$ at $B^{\prime} 
eq B$. Also, let $\overline{B C}$ intersect $\omega_{2}$ at $C^{\prime} 
eq C$. Let $X 
eq A$ be on $\omega_{1}$ such that $B^{\prime} X=B^{\prime} A$. Let $Y 
eq A$ be on $\omega_{2}$ such that $C^{\prime} A=C^{\prime} Y$. Let $X, Y, A$ all lie on one line $h$. Find the length of $P A$.
